		</OptionalItemsName1><OptionalItemsText1 type="dhtml" label="Optional Item Text 1" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p><strong>Stephen Allen</strong>, a native of Ogden, Utah, received degrees in piano performance from the Eastman School of Music and San Jose State University.&nbsp; He earned his doctoral degree in piano pedagogy and literature from Indiana University, where he minored in both music education and musicology. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; His solo performances include appearances throughout North America, including tours of Yokosuka and Yokohama, Japan, where he presented master classes for Music International-Japan (associated with the National Federation of Music Clubs) as guest performer and adjudicator.&nbsp; As an active chamber musician he has performed frequently, including invitations to perform at the International Double Reed Society.<br /><br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In 2004 he was recognized for teaching excellence with the University Faculty Association Faculty Award and in 2009 he was awarded the BYU-Idaho Distinguished Faculty Award.&nbsp; Dr. Allen, NCTM, is the recipient of the Idaho Music Teachers Association Teacher of the Year Award.&nbsp; <br /><br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A frequent adjudicator and avid educator, Dr. Allen, has presented in numerous state and regional workshops and conferences. &nbsp;He is currently at Brigham Young University-Idaho, where he has taught since 1986. <br /><br /></p>]]></OptionalItemsText1><OptionalItemsName2 label="Optional Item Title 2" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></OptionalItemsName2><OptionalItemsText2 type="dhtml" label="Optional Item Text 2" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[]]></OptionalItemsText2><OptionalItemsName3 label="Optional Item Title 3" readonly="false" hidden=